00:02:12,541 --> 00:02:15,436
is that she is compelled /kəmˈpɛl 强迫/ by 
the same curiosity /ˌkjʊərɪˈɒsɪtɪ/

42
00:02:15,436 --> 00:02:24,361
that helped ensure the continuation /kənˌtɪnjʊˈeɪʃən/ of
her species /ˈspiːʃiːz 物种/ for millions of years before.

43
00:02:24,361 --> 00:02:30,181
In the wild, cats needed sharp claws
for climbing, hunting, and self-defense.

44
00:02:30,181 --> 00:02:34,778
Sharpening their claws on nearby surfaces
kept them conditioned and ready,

45
00:02:34,778 --> 00:02:36,901
helped stretch /strɛtʃ 有弹性的/ their back and leg muscles,

46
00:02:36,901 --> 00:02:39,321
and relieve some stress, too.

47
00:02:39,321 --> 00:02:41,451
So, it's not that Grizmo hates your couch /kaʊtʃ 长沙发椅/,

48
00:02:41,451 --> 00:02:42,287
chair,

49
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,272
ottoman /ˈɒtəmən 软垫凳 土耳其人/,

50
00:02:43,272 --> 00:02:44,017
pillows /ˈpɪləʊ 枕头/,

51
00:02:44,017 --> 00:02:44,794
curtains /ˈkɜːtən 窗帘/,

52
00:02:44,794 --> 00:02:47,499
and everything else 
you put in her environment.

53
00:02:47,499 --> 00:02:52,134
She's ripping /rɪp 撕/ these things to shreds
and keeping her claws in tip-top shape

54
00:02:52,134 --> 00:02:57,763
because this is exactly what her ancestors
did in order to survive.

55
00:02:57,763 --> 00:02:59,506
As animals that were preyed upon,

56
00:02:59,506 --> 00:03:01,883
cats evolved to not get caught,

57
00:03:01,883 --> 00:03:06,195
and in the wild, the cats that were 
the best at avoiding predators thrived /θraɪv 繁荣/.

58
00:03:06,195 --> 00:03:07,651
So at your house today,

59
00:03:07,651 --> 00:03:11,449
Grizmo is an expert /ˈɛkspɜːt/
at squeezing /skwiːz 挤压/ into small spaces

60
00:03:11,449 --> 00:03:15,663
and seeking out and hiding
